'''Humboldt Mountains''' ({{coord|71|45|S|11|30|E|}}) is a group of [[mountain]]s immediately west of the [[Petermann Ranges]], forming the westernmost portion of the [[Wohlthat Mountains]] in [[Queen Maud Land]]. They were discovered and mapped by the [[Third German Antarctic Expedition]] (1938-1939), led by Capt. [[Alfred Ritscher]], who named them for [[Alexander von Humboldt]], famed German naturalist and geographer of the first half of the nineteenth century.
